            h4.
              FAQs


            p.question
              |Why has Cambridge Ahead produced this Cluster Map and how does it differ from the previous version?
            p.answer
              |It is only now (Feb 2016) that it has been possible to draw together accurate financial data covering the full range of Cambridge companies, both those based in Cambridge, and those trading in it. Find out #[a(href="http://www.cambridgeahead.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/About-Companies-Data-on-the-CCM.pdf", target="_blank") how we define them and the company data provided]. The map is also different from earlier versions because the data and the map presentation of it is not just for the Tech sector, but for all the other economic sectors too.

            p.question
              |What is the source of the data that has been analysed to produce the Cluster Map?

            p.answer
              |The source of the data is the FAME database produced by Bureau Van Dijk which includes over 3 million active UK-based companies and a further 6 million that are dormant or who have died.

            p.question
              |What is the definition of a Knowledge-Intensive (KI) company?
            p.answer
              |We classify KI sectors as Information technology and communications; Life science and healthcare; High-tech Manufacturing; and Knowledge intensive services.

            p.question
              |What is a &lsquo;scale-up&rsquo; company?
            p.answer
              |A &lsquo;scale-up&rsquo; is an enterprise with average annualised growth in employees or turnover greater than 20 per cent per annum over a three year period, and with more than 10 employees at the beginning of the observation period. (See the #[a(href='http://www.scaleupreport.org/', target="_blank") Scale-up Report], November 2014)

            p.question
              |What methodology has been used to create the map?
            p.answer
              |Please see the CBR database methodology #[a(href='http://www.cambridgeahead.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/CBR-Database-Methodology-Feb-2016.pdf', target="_blank") here].

            p.question
              |My company entry has an incorrect entry. How do I get it fixed?
            p.answer
              |Please complete this #[a(href='http://www.cambridgeahead.co.uk/camclustermap/contact', target="_blank") form]. The correction will be made in the next planned upload of data.

            p.question
              |My company isn&rsquo;t listed. Why not?
            p.answer
              |If a company is registered outside Cambridge but has not provided its trading address i.e. postcode in Cambridge, then it is likely that it will not be feature within the Cluster Map. There are some non-Cambridge registered companies included on the database, despite not showing their Cambridge operation, because we know they are here. However, to justify the effort of doing that our present policy is that the company has to qualify as being both KI and have ten or more employees.

            p.question
              |Why don&rsquo;t you publish the full addresses of companies?
            p.answer
              |It is not necessary &ndash; this map is not a postal directory but an analysis of performance data. By limiting the address to postal code we ensure that we have a good location indicator.

            p.question
              |How often is the data updated?
            p.answer
              |Typically we intend of refresh the data, including corrections, every three months.

            p.question
              |I am a researcher and want access to the full dataset so that I can make my own analysis. How can I get this?
            p.answer
              |You have to become an accredited researcher. To do this, please complete this #[a(href='http://www.cambridgeahead.co.uk/camclustermap/contact', target="_blank") form]. Dr Andy Cosh of the CBR will be in touch.

            p.question
              |Where can I find out more background about the Cluster Map?
            p.answer
              |Please visit #[a(href="http://www.cambridgeahead.co.uk/camclustermap", target="_blank") www.cambridgeahead.co.uk/camclustermap]

